other_tests.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis; normal liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands; bilateral subcentimeter renal hypodensities likely representing simple cysts; equivocal subtle fat stranding in the region of the proximal sigmoid colon raising question of mild sigmoid diverticulitis; no adjacent fluid collections or free air; enlarged prostate measuring up to 5.8 cm; no abdominal aortic aneurysm; calcification and chronic thrombus in the infrarenal abdominal aorta; atheromatous plaque in the proximal celiac artery.
